OL,6,FHe told the defendant: "You will be
OL,7,Ftreated fairly and justly ` I can make
OL,8,Fno promises, but this is a very
OL,9,Funusual case and because of that I
OL,10,Frather suspect a very unusual sentence
OL,11,Fmay be passed.
OL,13,F"I will say no more at the moment but
OL,14,FI do understand the very considerable
OL,15,Fdifficulties that you have.
OL,17,F"This case is a tragedy on the grand
OL,18,Fscale, from first to last."
